diff:1521063456:1521063203:=110,114c110,114%0a%3c *The staff member views your request on their dashboard. They can opt to Approve, Deny, or Return a request.%0a%3c *Approve or Deny - this will return the request to the player for them to close. This is so that a player can know what happened with their request.%0a%3c *Return - This returns the request back to the player to update for whatever reason.%0a%3c *The ST can (and should) provide a note to the request when they take an action on it.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> The staff member views your request on their dashboard. They can opt to Approve, Deny, or Return a request.%0a> Approve or Deny - this will return the request to the player for them to close. This is so that a player can know what happened with their request.%0a> Return - This returns the request back to the player to update for whatever reason.%0a> The ST can (and should) provide a note to the request when they take an action on it.%0a> %0a116,118c116,118%0a%3c *Review and Close your character’s Approved or Rejected request.%0a%3c *Update Requests that have been returned and resubmit: Attach > New Note to provide a response. Actions > *Submit Request to resubmit.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Review and Close your character’s Approved or Rejected request.%0a> Update Requests that have been returned and resubmit: Attach > New Note to provide a response. Actions > Submit Request to resubmit.%0a> %0a122,127c122,126%0a%3c %0a%3c *The Bluebook is your personal character record, and where you keep track of your character’s achievements, progress towards goals, participation in scenes, and important events. For those familiar with “Character Threads,” this equates to the non-request use.%0a%3c %0a%3c *The Bluebook is located under Utilities > Player Utilities, then select Interface for the Character. From the Interface page, Tools > Bluebook > New%0a%3c %0a%3c *Click on Tools > Bluebook to view your Bluebook Dashboard.%0a---%0a> The Bluebook is your personal character record, and